               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-200-person1928">
                  JOSEPH 
                  HOWLE
               <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1928" type="surname" value="HOWLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1928" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1928" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290409-200-viclabel1139" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-200-victim1927 t18290409-200-viclabel1139"></join>, and live in Warwick-street, Golden-square. I was in the <placeName id="t18290409-200-crimeloc1140">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-200-crimeloc1140" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-200-crimeloc1140" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-200-off1137 t18290409-200-crimeloc1140"></join>, about eleven o'clock in the morning of the 4th of March; a gentleman touched me, and said I had had my pocket picked - I turned, and saw my handkerchief in Stretton's hand; he was in the custody of the gentleman, who told me of it - I began to reprimand him, and the gentleman said, "That is not the one that took it - I'll fetch the man that took it;" he went and fetched the other prisoner.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did Stretton hear the conversation? A. No question of it; I did not take hold of him; he was not allowed to go any distance; he never stirred from me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-200-person1929">
                  FRANCIS 
                  COSTER
               <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1929" type="surname" value="COSTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1929" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-person1929" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an oilman, and live in the Strand. I was coming down Drury-lane, and saw the prosecutor - the two prisoners were behind him; Forest had his hand in his pocket, and took out the handkerchief, which he passed to Stretton; I immediately ran and seized Stretton - I told the prosecutor he had been robbed; I then ran and took Forest.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had not Stretton been allowed to go a distance? A. Yes, five or six doors - that was after Mr. Howle had seen him and I had fetched Forest; he went about twenty-five yards or thereabouts - he did not attempt to run; it was not possible that the handkerchief could have dropped on the ground, and the other take it up.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>FOREST'S Defence. I had been on an errand for Mr. Reece, where I work; this man came and touched me, and said he wanted me - that I was the person who had picked his pocket; Mr. Howle told me I might go about my business, but this man called me a pickpocket, and then gave me in charge.</p>
               <p>STRETTON's Defence. I was going along, and heard a person say, "You are robbed;" I saw a handkerchief upon the ground, and picked it up - a gentleman came up, and said, "Take charge of him;" I had not my senses at the moment, I was so confused; I did drop it down - he then brought this other young man, and said I might go away, then he called me again, and said, "The other one has been saucy, and the gentleman is determined to give you both into custody."</p>
               <p>The prisoners received a good character.</p>
               <p>STRETTON - <rs id="t18290409-200-verdict1141" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-verdict1141" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30.</p>
               <p>FOREST - <rs id="t18290409-200-verdict1142" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290409-200-verdict1142" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
